Both required files are written to the bundle directory.

- `transcript.json` — 25 iterations, 36 hypotheses, 36 analyses; validates against `transcript_schema.json`.
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative synthesis of the analyses.

Headline findings: the strongest predictor of `objective_response` is the ordinal `feature_057` (response 21.3%/15.5%/11.2% across levels 0/1/2; adjusted OR 0.68 per level, p≈1e-96). Independent continuous predictors push as expected (`feature_011`, `feature_006`, `feature_092`, `feature_063` negative; `feature_099` positive). The only strong positive binary predictor is `feature_035` (OR 1.43 adjusted, consistent across `feature_057` strata). Age and insurance show no association; race shows a small but significant residual omnibus effect (LR p = 0.009, ~2–3 pt spread) not explained by the measured clinical variables. Only one pairwise interaction reached p<0.05: `feature_099 × feature_035` (the feature_035 benefit attenuates at higher feature_099). Full multivariable AUC = 0.597.
